{"author":{"id":"4bb6c1767e50694cfde61856db22bf137d1651e8a0b5ca858c486db3dd02f280"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1774313165,"nonce":"2zaV6f+lYDJsZPog/fWE/+sCtXU=","message":"## Meta-optimization of discount function (deferred)\n\nIf the running cost + softmin approaches don't produce sufficient peak velocity differences, consider bi-level optimization:\n\n- Inner loop: train network with parameterized discount d(t; phi)\n- Outer loop: adjust phi to maximize reaching performance + peak velocity difference (SISU=1 vs SISU=0)\n- Function class: piecewise linear with 4 knots (go cue, step 40, step 80, trial end), monotonicity constrained\n- Outer objective must constrain reaching performance at BOTH SISU values to prevent gaming (freeze at SISU=0)\n- Validation: train FRESH networks with optimized discount to confirm non-pathological\n- Practical: ~10-20 short training runs via Bayesian optimization over 4 parameters\n\nLiterature: Bechtle et al. (2019) \"Meta-Learning via Learned Loss\", Xu et al. (2018) \"Meta-Gradient RL\"\n\nStatus: deferred pending results from running cost and softmin experiments.\n\nCo-authored-by: Claude Opus 4.6 \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e","files":null}]}